			{
				"type": "Comment",
				"start": 0,
				"end": 483,
				"data": "\n\tAn EMPTY <textarea> hugged by an inline <label>. The whitespace-sensitive element has no\n\tcontent, so nothing at the label's boundary is whitespace-significant: the <label> lays out\n\tblock-style like any other inline element, and only the <textarea>'s own attributes react to\n\tprint width. Prettier instead dangles the label's closing delimiter, and the `</label` suffix\n\tit adds to the textarea line is what pushes the attributes over — see\n\tprettier_variant_label_dangle.\n"
			},
			{
				"type": "Text",
				"start": 483,
				"end": 485,
				"raw": "\n\n",
				"data": "\n\n"
			},
